Feeling like you’re stuck at your squat max?

Adding paused squats will help you squat heavier because there is
-more time under tension
-more control of the movement
-increases core strength
and overall helps you focus on pushing out of the hole.

I love incorporating these once a week because I can notice how well I focus on my movement and I can feel those muscles being worked during my squat.

I recommend starting with a 2 sec pause at the bottom of your squat & lower weight. After mastering your form and technique, make it your goal to add 5-10 lbs each week 🔥

Cable goblet squats are so underrated 😮‍💨

Besides having my quads on absolute fire, I love how much it forces me to tighten up and strengthen my core with the movement.

You are fighting (x) amount of lbs and the resistance of the cable really makes you focus on a tight core and correct squat form.

This also really helps me work on my “stripper squat” reps when I struggle with heavier weight. 
A stripper squat is when your hips fly up before your chest forcing you to lean forward and push up the weight mostly with your lower back.

Try them out and let me know how you like them 💖

Glute RDLS vs Hammie RDLS 🔥

The bent knees make all the difference in your romanians deadlifts to focus on the glutes.

You DON’T want to squat your RDLS but also get enough of the knees bending to get a good stretch in your glutes!

Those core memories get my ass up real fucking fast. Starting from scratch and no handouts.. i’ve made it happen every single time. 

I can’t believe @athenafitclub is taking it to a whole other level this summer.

Quad focused vs Glute focused 🔥

These two often get a little confusing but these are my main cues!! 

Quad focused:
- Keep torso straight 
- Chest high
- Go straight down into a squat

Glutes: 
- Lean torso forward
- Tuck in your chin 
- Hinge hips back as you travel down

Hope this helps you guys out ❤️‍🔥

My favorite exercise to target my lower back is the back extensions! 

This back extension is certainly different than a glute/hammies hyperextension.

To target your lower back muscles, make sure you keep your toes pointed forward and travel all the way down and up with a straight torso. 

By strengthening your lower back, you will notice your compound lifts will start to feel a lot better and the back pain you experience while you exercise will subside!! 👏🏽

It is also very important to train your core if you are someone who feels their lower back muscles engaging more than the muscle you are trying to target!

Hope this helps besties 💗🔥

No better feeling than looking in the mirror and seeing your hard work pay off 🥹🫶🏼

I will be super honest with you all and say nutrition has been my biggest factor in seeing results.

I try my best to stay on top of my protein intake daily and to show up to my workouts no matter how I feel and get my cardio done.

I give my self some wiggle room on the weekends but I make sure to jump back on it. 

Preparation, organization and focus!

Write down your “non-negotiables” and make it happen not matter what gets in the way! 👏🏽💗

3 THINGS I NEVER SKIP TO BUILD MY GLUTES 🍑⬇️

1. Eating enough protein daily:
I will say this is the BIGGEST one for me. I have noticed my glutes building when I have been consistent with my nutrition. If it’s hard for you to accomplish, try to start slow and slowly work your way up! Natural protein sources over protein powders all day 👏🏽

2. Isolating my glutes at least 2x per week:
Although full body workouts can be fun and intense, sometimes what we really need to do is put together a routine of 4-6 exercises and focus on performing intentional reps. Slow down and feel the burn 🔥

3. Rest:
I used to workout my glutes 3-4x a week and even then I didn’t notice the shape or growth like I do now. 
Giving your muscles enough time to recover and rebuild is very important. It’s great to train hard but give your body time to recover 🫶🏼

It really be like that during these circuits 🥲😭
But MAN do they feel amazing after completing!!

I encourage you to get out of your comfort zone and try one of these soon 🫶🏼
